Method Detail

onCreate

public void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState)
Called when the activity is first created; it ensures that the IPTables is installed, generates and launches a script string based on settings, sets the view, and creates buttons for launching ViewRulesActivity, EditRulesActivity, and ViewLogActivity.

initialString

private java.lang.String initialString(java.lang.String input)
Returns the initial string for the script. The script does the following:

1. Removes any existing log rules to prevent duplications and allow for there to be no logging.

2. Removes and creates rules which allow DNS traffic in order to ensure their existence without duplication.

3. Creates a chain named FETCH. If the chain already exists, nothing will happen.

4. Removes and creates rules to jump to the FETCH chain in order to ensure their existence without duplication.

Parameters:
input - string containing previously generated script. Should be empty at this point.
Returns:
string consisting of input + initial string rules.

setLogging

private java.lang.String setLogging(java.lang.String input)
Returns string consisting of the input string plus either nothing or logging rules. If logging is selected in the settings, then rules implementing logging are added to the string. Otherwise, nothing is added to the string.

Parameters:
input - string containing previously generated script.
Returns:
string consisting of input + either logging rules or nothing.

setBlock

private java.lang.String setBlock(java.lang.String input)
Returns string consisting of the input string plus commands to set the standard policy for input and output based on the settings. If blocking is set in the settings, the default policy will be to drop all traffic; otherwise the default policy will be to accept all traffic.

Parameters:
input - string containing previously generated script.
Returns:
string consisting of input + commands for policy

sendNotification

public void sendNotification()
Used to send system notification that the IPTables binary has been installed. This is done by starting the HoneyBadgerNotify activity.

onCreateOptionsMenu

public boolean onCreateOptionsMenu(Menu menu)
Launches an options menu when the device options button is selected. The basic structure of this method is from the book Pro Android 2.

onOptionsItemSelected

public boolean onOptionsItemSelected(MenuItem item)
Used to handle selection of items in options menu. Starts activity for selected item. If "Settings" is selected, then EditPreferencesActivity is started. If "Clear Log" is selected, then LogDBAdapter is used to clear the log. If "Add Rule" is selected, then EditRulesActivity is started.
